track_notes: Mt. Willingdon is accessed from Devon Lakes.  There are two ways to get to Devon Lakes; a backpackers route through Fish Lakes, or a climbers route over Quartzite Col.  This route is the later.  Park at the Mosquito Creek parking lot and hike up the well maintained trail along Mosquito Creek.  After about an hour, you will leave the trail and it will be bushwhacking the rest of the journey.  There will be places where you will see signs of previous visitors and some places where there may even be a faint trail but mostly you will follow the creek to Quartzite Pass which will drop off very steeply on the East side.  You will drop down over 400 meters to a vast alpine meadow that you will cross toward Devon Lakes, eventually finding a trail that will take you the last few kilometers to Devon Lakes.  From the Lakes, you will follow the west ridge to the summit.  There will be a lot of scrambling and an exposed section near the summit that has a fixed rope for security. Grade MN9, YDS 5.2
